review_blob: This dark beer is heavy on malts, and light on coffee flavor.  It is very drinkable, but a tad watered down in my opinion.

This beers taste can bvest be characterized by the taste on sour mayonaise.  The smell is much more pleasant, reminiscent of the floor of a men's locker room. This fine brew is on par with terrible college beers for flavor, but way over priced.  Its reassuring knowing germany has awful beers too.
Nice fresh crisp taste.  Very clean with little aftertaste.  Enjoyable experience.

Wow definately a great sweet stout.  The sweetest one I have ever tried to date.  Sugary/Malasses aftertaste, with a thick malasses taste to compliment the roasted aroma and flavor.  Excellent pour too with a nice head color.  Excellent speciman!  One of my new favorite stouts.

Most carbonated stout I have ever seen.  Good clean crisp cocoa and roasted flavor.  Roasted malts really shine through.  This beer is near explosive.  Do NOT pour it into a glass.  It will become 90% head no matter how well you pour.  Drink it from the bottle.  I learned the hard way.  excellent flavor, and oder makes this worth trying.

Not nearly as good as the tennents scotch ale.  This reminds me too much of a cheap domestic american standard.  Flavor is skunky, and aftertaste resembles watery bud light.  Not only was I unimpressed, I was disgusted at this speciman.
This is a dryer stout without much sweetness.  Nice fullbody, and roasted malts are most prevalent.  The aftertaste is very minimal particularly for a stout.  Not many lingering flavors.
beer_name: Wye Valley Dorothy Goodbodys Wholesome Stout

review_blob: Holy hop-tastic batman.  This is pure hops with a little bitter taste to compliment.  This is the hoppiest beer I have sampled in my 120ish ratings. If you want hops, you want this.  If you don't care for hops, stay away, very far away.

Smelled wonderful, but didn't taste as good as it smelled.  Alcohol content is masked beautifully.  Complex fruity taste with hints of natural oak and wood like flavors.  Unique, hard to describe aftertaste, and wonderful think brown color.  Definately not worth $10 a bottle, but it is a pleasant sampling experience.

beer_brewer_name: Yakima Brewing And Malting Co./Bert Grants Real Ales
review_blob: Good solid porter.  Robust malts, and a hint of roasted coffee.  Also a very slight hint of chocolate.  Not very sweet or bitter.  I would describe this as a middle of the road neutral tasting porter.  Definately worth trying.

A good solid stout.  Very crisp and clean with little to no aftertaste.  Would never turn one of these bad boys down.  An enjoyable stout indeed.  Not the best, but definately worth a taste for any stout enthusiast.

This beer is more carbinated then I expected.  The bubbles never stopped eminating from the bottom of the glass.  It is an enjoyable beer, but not one of my favorites.  Not as good as the red.  Pretty amber/dark brown color, and amazing head and bubblage.  Definately a great beer, but I felt like something was missing.  Not as complex as some of the other chimay beers.
Alcohol was masked terribly.  Unfortunately the flavor was masked fairly well.  This is a bland over priced import.  The bottle was beautiful, but the taste left much to be desired.
Don't care for original sam adams lager at all.  Cherry and stout and a lot of the other brands are amazingly good, but the lager is skunky to my taste.  Bland, and way too hoppy for my tastes.

I can see where someone could really like this beer, but it just isnt my style.  Tastes like it is just missing something I can't put my finger on.  Not really bitter at all.  Hints of creaminess, but not prominent.  Tasted quite bland to me.  Unimpressive.
Strong hints of malases and nutmeg.  Sweeter then expected.  Nice looking bottle and great looking beer in glass with a nice brown color and full head.  Very low on carbonation.
Fosters, Australian for wombat piss.  Seriously, I think this is just budweiser in a different container.  I'd rather not drink then consume this or budweiser!  They do have good ad's though.
Watered down flavorless beer.  No sign of wheat anywhere, or anything else for that matter. Not enjoyable at all.  Don't kid yourself, this isn't beer -- It is yellow tap water.
This is a nice red-brown creamy ale.  Fruit is prevalent, and the bottle is cool.  I was pleasantly surprised.  Definately would drink again.
worst of the keystone lot.  One of my worst college memories along with waking up in that guys backyard.  Good thing he didn't have a shotgun.

Had this out of the tap at a local brewery.  Very yellow beer.  Looked like dirty well water.  I prefer tap beer, but this seemed watered down.  I can't be certain if the keg was strugglingly low or not though.  I'll give it the benefit of the doubt.  No wheat flavor at all, and much paler than I expected.  Not worth the price.
Dark roasted coffee porter. Destinctly bitter flavor. flavors nicely blended and compliment each other well.  Thumbs up!
Good crisp porter.  Made from the freshly polluted waters of the all too often burning cuyahoga river.  The river water might not be drinkable, but this finely crafter porter is definately worth it.
Better then Molsom golden.  Still american Standard style doesn't tickle my fancy.  Drinkable, but not reccommended.
Better then bud, but not much else.  Best drinken when aquired freely.  Do not spend money on this garbage.
I love the Dark St. Pauli Girl, but this lager is terrible.  Aftertaste is very unpleasant and is is overall quite a skunky speciman.
May as well be bud! Perhaps the worst thing to come out of Canada since Alanis Morrisette.  Yuck!

Nice and creamy.  It has a creamy aftertate too.  One of the best aftertastes I have seen on any beer.  They claim this is from coors, but it's too good to really be coors, I think they are importing it.

Complex assortment of flavors.  Kind of Foldgers meets Sanka at a monster truck rally, and they decide to get drunk. This porter goes well complimenting food.  Dark rugged flavor, and not the least bit smooth.  This beer's flavor has an attitude.
Warsteiner = German for Budweiser.  This beer was seriously watered down, and mostly tasteless.  Not reccommended.
One of the more drinkable American domestics.  Better than Bud any day of the week.  I like to refer to this as poor man's killians.

Good clean favor.  I think this beer is a little under-appreciated.  Nice hints of fruits and nuts.  I would best describe this beer as a pale drk beer.  It has a lot of characteristics of a dark beer, but it isn't dark in the least bit.  Definately worth trying.  I liked it better the colder it was.

Not good, but tolerable to drink.  This is not an average light beer. I bought one 6 pack of michelob black and tan, and one of ultra.  The ultra actually weighed less.  not only is it light, but it weighs less physically. Simply amazing, but the taste is anything but amazing.
Very close to Heiniken.  Problem being I dont like Heiniken very much.  I had this in a 1.5 litre container.  The container was much better than the beer contained within.

Wow, I am pleasantly surprised.  By far the best michelob or for that matter michelob product I have ever had.  This beer has flavor.  Unlike most domestic beers it has genuine flavor.  Hints of chocolate and nut and carmel.  I had my roommate try this, and didnt let her read the label.  She really liked it, and then I revealed it was michelob and she was indeed surprised.  Definately try this one.
Has a hint of fruit in it, and is a bit bitter, but not too bitter.  It has a good finish to it.  I enjoyed this beer.

Surprisingly not even as good of a red beer as killians, or an other red beer I have had.  This one was a little bit of a disappointment.  Petes has some good beers, but this one is not among them.  Average at best.
Not a big fan of the helles style.  Not many different flavors going on with this beer.  Pretty bland in my opinion.  Most of the other Petes beers are much better than this one.

This might be my favorite petes brew yet.  I love the raspberry flavor.  It really stands out.  I couldnt taste the nutmeg as advertized, but the raspberries made this beer well worth drinknig.  Not too sweet, just plain good.  One of the best aromas i have smelled on a beer also.
Very good for a macrobrew.  The nut flavor really does come threw.  The flavor matches the smell well.

Hands down the best macrobrewed light beer I have had.  It has descent alcohol by volume for a light beer also.  Hardly any aftertaste, and surprisingly crisp. Six dollars for a twelve pack of bottles.  Yet it is drinkable.  Tastes as though it would be awful in a can, but I have a feeling this is going to be my new off paycheck week beer.

Had to re-rate.  This beer used to be good, but with each ensuing time I drink it, it seems to loose its luster.  Still the best thing going in Pittsbugh.  That is, when it is fresh.  A local pub that carries this often lets it get skunky.  It smells good, and is a descent beer, but it doesnt compare with the worlds finest.
I could taste the bitterness, but I have had more bitter beers.  It only vaguely reminded me of an English bitter ale.  I prefer the Blonde ale by redhook, but this is descent.

This has possibly the weakest aroma of any porter I have tried.  However, the taste is definately there.  It isnt very sweet and I would have to agree with venom that it has a very earthy feeling to it.  It was one of the most bitter porters I have tried.  I liked it a lot and would drink it again.
A descent beer.  I would drink it again.  The lemon taste is definately noticable, but not overbearing.  Excellent beer for the cheap price.

beer_brewer_name: Wild Goose Brewery (Frederick Brewing Company/Flying Dog)
review_blob: a good plain porter.  nothing really special, but I liked the simpleness to it.  It is a very basic porter taste.  A good beginers beer.

A descent stout, but it pales in comparison to the world wide stout.  This beer is easier to find and worth drinking when it is accessible.  Tastes more like coffee than perhaps any other stout I have tried.

Very complex taste and it appears to me that the most noticible is vanilla.  The alcohol isnt masked very well in this, and the 11% alcohol content sneaks up on you quickly.  Definately a quality brew, but it is over priced.

Annother good beer from Dogfish.  This one is worthy of trying like all of the other dogfish beers.  This brewery definatly knows whats going on.  Not much raison taste to this, but it is a good lager with a fruity notes.

This beer was bloody good.  I thoroughly enjoyed it.  The alcohol was well masked.  It is strong and damn good.  It tasted kind of like a wine that met a stout and had a party.  I really enjoyed this beer and recommend it to anyone.  Dont drink too many or youll be needing help home.
